So far, terrible service. My diabetes nutrition center even warned me that they often forget to send supplies and the front desk sighs when I mention them. Unfortunately I didn't heed their warning and called mini pharmacy too late and ran out of my diabetes testing strips and lancets. I called, was on hold for about 20mins before speaking with someone only to be told they didn't know why my shipment didn't ship. The rep said she'd have someone call me back later with an update.

I got a call later that day just confirming my order. No apology or explanation of why my shipment didn't go out. I was down to my last strip and had to request they send it faster than their 6-7 business day shipping. They changed it to 2-3 business days. 102405320006617588972<//UserId.>
<gmap_id>0x80c2c8a1e00ad0d7:0xf3e011fe792819d9< /gmap_id><pictures>None</pictures>< Review>
Little wonder this pharmacy has 2 star rating. Most, like me would give it ZERO stars but we are required to give it one star in order to write the review.

When you call this place -- ifs IFFY at best - which means you might wait on the line for LONG time, probably be sent to voice mail, may not get ANY response at ALL.

If , after you finally get someone on the other end of the line, you complain, they will give you "extensions" so you can supposedly get through to them on subsequent calls (I have 3).  When you dial the extensions, you may or may not get a live person.  I called and dialed ALL THREE OF THE EXTENSIONS I have last week and got a recording with each one.

So, I decided to call and leave a message as they request, with name and date of birth.  This was on Wed. last.  Today is Saturday and still haven't heard from them.  I called today (although I suspect they are closed) and left another message.  I will also be calling again on Monday.

The reason I gave 2 stars and not one is that when they DO actually talk to you and get your info they manage to get your script out pretty fast - like the next day or so (but that is the responsibility of EVERY pharmacy)

Honestly, I agree with another reviewer who said this pharmacy should be shut down.

I filed a complaint with the California State Board of Pharmacy.  I will express my grievance and direct them to this site for confirmation of their poor service.  I suggest others who visit this site and are not happy with the service they are receiving should do the same.  Just Google the name of the board and you will directed to the site.  It doesn't take long and is pretty straight forward.  Their license # is PHY 57214.

Additionally, I will speak to my Endo who sent my RX to them to be filled and let him know in no uncertain terms as to how lousy their service is (will direct him to these Google reviews) and request that he send my RX to another pharmacy for fulfillment.

Will update after they reply to my last call, although at this point NOTHING they say or do will warrant adding stars, if anything perhaps losing one.
______

Well its Tuesday and no one has called me back and script has not been filled.  I made multiple calls today and left multiple messages on multiple extensions (the ones they gave me to assure me someone would answer and take care of business)

Once again, I recommend everyone having problems with this Pharmacy to file their complaint with the State Board.  You can do it on line, its a simple form, and will only take you a few minutes.
_____

I just noticed that this company has 1.5 star Yelp rating with 90 reviews.
---------------------------------

Edit: Since writing this scathing review I have to say that the company has  managed to deliver my diabetic supplies in a timely manner and I no longer have anything to complain about.  I also noticed that their Yelp review has gone from 1.5 stars to 2 stars.  I hope they keep up the good work and make their customers happy, because that is what business is all about.<//Review>

<name>Ally A.</name>< review>
I was diagnosed with gestational diabetes; my doctor set up getting my meter, strips, and lancets with Mini Pharmacy. My first order came in overnight and I had no issues. I tried placing a refill order a few days before I ran out of strips, but the rep told me I had to wait until the exact date that my order ran out before they could send me a second order. I was grilled on how often I was testing, how many strips I received in my first order, etc. She was able to send me a few sample boxes of strips in case I ran out. My third order was supposedly sent out overnight but I did not get it. I had to call and ask where it was, I was told it would arrive the next day. For my last order; I called and placed an order that I assumed would arrive the next day just as my previous orders had arrived. I never had to ask for overnight delivery. I didn't get the order, so I called and the rep told me it was mailed regular mail and could take 3-5 days to arrive to me. She told me that processing determines how your order is mailed out unless you ask it to be overnight-ed. I wish I knew I had to request overnight delivery because I cannot wait 5 days for strips to come in, especially when I can only order on the date my previous order expired. I am not allowed to skip testing days per my doctor's orders. The rep also told me she has delivery confirmation it arrived to my box, however there was no note that I had a package waiting for me at the post office and it was not delivered at my door. She told me she would need to contact USPS to verify the delivery and then they can mail another order out. That is fine but they have no signature confirmation to verify someone signed for the package, the post man may have ended up setting it at someone else's door or putting it in someone else's box. Meanwhile I have 1 day left of strips to somehow get me through the next 2 days. I work as a call center manager for an online traffic school, and if I had any of the reps I have spoke with working with me, they would be getting their termination papers. I give this company 2 stars only because one rep was able to give me some sample boxes of strips, otherwise they would get 1 star. My advice: find a better company that has a better record of deliveries and has better customer service.< /review>

< Rate>
1<//Rate>
< review>
I was not offered any other pharmacy to choose by my gestational diabetes nurse. As a pharmacist, this bothered me at first (since patients technically have the right to use the pharmacy of their choice), but I figured maybe I should give this pharmacy a try (maybe it was cheaper through my insurance). I got my first set of test strips and lancets delivered and left on my doorstep in a timely manner when I was not home, but I was not as concerned since at that time, the temperature outside was around mid-70 degrees Fahrenheit (my test strips are not allowed to be in temperatures below 36 degrees or above 86 degrees Fahrenheit or risk inaccurate blood sugar readings). Yesterday, I called Mini Pharmacy about my refill and concern with the temperature outside, especially with it being summer in southern California with high temperatures close to 90's or more. I was told that they will deliver my refill with their own pharmacy driver (not their contracted mail delivery carrier) on Monday before noon when I would most likely be home (and less likely be hot outside). I get the delivery left on my doorstep today instead (Saturday) at 84 degree weather by OnTrac, I have the Ring doorbell which told me they delivered around 1:25 pm, and I had to rush home from a family event to bring my test strips indoors before it got hotter (high today is expected to be 89 degrees).

Even though I managed to bring it indoors before it got to 86 degrees, I was disturbed that my package was delivered not as promised and without a signature to verify I was home (even the outside box label said "Signature Required"). What would have happened if this was a more delicate medication or if I was not there in time with the high heat outside? This should be my last prescription fill for this pregnancy, but if I ever need to go through this again, I would rather request my health provider send my prescription to a nearby pharmacy where I can physically pick up my order in an indoor environment.</review>

<review>I felt that once you've informed them that you cannot afford a $900 brake job that they (or at least Chase) starts talking condescendingly or becomes short with you. Suddenly I felt as though I was wasting his time asking questions. The final negative tone came when I asked for the cost breakdown and was told it was stapled to my receipt. That being said with a tone of annoyance is unacceptable. I was reading the technicians notes when he said something and stapled something to the receipt.

The waiting area is very nice, very modern, up to date with every phone cord imaginable to charge your phone, reclining seats, etc.

Upon walking in I waited approx 5-10 minutes for  someone to come in and help me. A full time person in the front would be very beneficial to them.

Upon receipt of my car my tires were not wiped down from the grease and grime from the technician. Now mind you, I live in the desert - the car isn't in the best shape and is dusty. But not grease and dust. It makes me believe that they felt less of a duty to care for the things they touched since my car was already an issue.

My door pocket had been gone through. They may state it was to find a lug nut, however, had they kept ransacking my car they would have found it in the center arm rest.

When I originally called them to discuss my brake issue, not once on the phone did Chase inform me there was a cost to inspect. I would have gone somewhere else. I paid it, so I did accept the cost, but let people know so they can make a choice before arriving.

Lastly, while waiting I learned they offer AAA discounts. I noted having AAA. Original estimate was over $900. What you see is the updated estimate with AAA included.

*I'm glad others have had such great experiences here. I did not and will not sugarcoat my experience, nor will I be rude about it either.

~CM</review>< Gmap_id>

I have been going to this shop for years and always have a great experience!  They really care about making their customers feel comfortable.

As a woman, I have always dreaded auto repair because it usually means going into scuzzy shops with scuzzy guys trying to tell you there are a million things wrong with your car.  But not here!  This shop is the cleanest shop I've ever been in and they are always very honest.  They let you know all the things that need to be fixed right away along with the things that may need to be fixed in the future.  But there is never any pressure to do anything more than what you want done.  Then as they do the repairs they keep you updated on the status so you're never wondering what's going on.

Also, I've been in for something small before where I just waited in the office and it is very cool in there.  There are comfortable couches, a large TV with cable and Netflix, and an electronics docking station so you can plug in your phone or laptop.  It's a very comfortable place to hang out while you're waiting.  I was able to feed and play with my baby and when I realized I had forgotten my diaper bag, the owner even had a stash of diapers for emergencies like that!  And they have a changing table in the bathroom which is very cool (You'd be surprised how many places do not have changing tables...).  Anyway, as a woman, I just feel very confident in taking my car here.

Everyone here is so friendly and helpful and the work on my car is always great!  I recommend this shop to all my friends and would never take my car anywhere else!< /review>

<rate>5<//rate><Text>I make it a point to keep up with maintenance on my car, which is a 2008 Nissan 350Z. I took it to the dealer for an oil change at 68,200 miles. They came back with about $1400 in services I supposedly needed. One of those services was a "slight oil leak in passenger side valve gasket". Another service was to have the spark plugs changed. They wanted $450 for the "leak" and $550 to change the spark plugs. I took the car back and headed for Aero Auto. I was a previous customer but hadn't been to them in awhile because I moved out of the area. Aero Auto thoroughly inspected my car, including all the things the dealer claimed it needed. David informed me that the spark plugs don't need to be changed until at least 100,000 miles, and the "leak" was just a couple of spots of oil on the top of the engine. He pulled the pan from under the car and it was completely dry with no oil on it, so there was no evidence of a leak. I was told my car was pristine and in excellent condition. < review>
I have worked at and managed repair shops all my life. I have always provided great customer service and this shop still exceeded my expectations! Not just one person, but EVERYONE at this shop has excellent customer service skills. I feel that if I was training a new hire I would first send them to Aero Auto to have their car serviced.
I have found that a repair shop is in a difficult position because everyone that walks through the door needs repairs or maintenance which was not in their monthly budget. Their car is the 2nd most important thing to them and when it breaks down their world comes to a grinding halt. As a repair shop adviser you generally do not talk to happy people which makes it difficult to turn the experience into a good one. This is where Aero Auto excels. Every time I left this place I was happier than when I went in. The fact that they take such good care of me shows they take great care of my car too.
If you are reading this, THERE IS NO REASON TO TAKE YOUR CAR ANYWHERE ELSE!<//review>

<review>Before you read my review If you need a smog don't go here. Star Station Smog Check is right down the street and they are nicer and cheaper! (plus they do free re-checks if you fail)

I am surprised that I have to write this review because of all the positive comments I see here on yelp, but today I did not have an experience like the others.

I came in for a smog check on my newly purchased 88 Vanagon and made sure to have all mechanical conditions checked out prior to ensure a proper passing test. After leaving them the car for 4 hours I received a call that the car passed the whole test but one evap item and that they could diagnose the problem for $118 and then find out how much it would be to fix. Before accepting the charge I decided to do some researching.

After goggling around I found that this portion of the test should not be performed because there is no accurate way of performing it (almost all fail on my type of van, due to inaccuracy because they have to fully pinch a hard plastic hose, which as we know you cannot fully seal a hard plastic object by pinching it) and that my car is fully acceptable to have "not applicable" in that section and "the state" does not have problem with it. Just to be sure I called around to 3 other smog stations in the area (obviously you can't believe everything you read on the internet) and they all informed me that the statement I read was true and they do not perform the test on that part due to the inaccuracies (this was not just to get me in there, I did go and "pass" right after my "fail" with Aero Auto Repair). This in combination with another bad experience I had (brought another car there to get smogged after a repair and it failed because the battery was disconnected the day before, if I would have known I would have waited, as to not pay another full price smog just to have me do nothing but drive it around for a week before I brought it in) made me feel like I was getting cheated, so I said that I don't believe the service that they were providing was fair and that I will have to report it to my credit card and they can decide if this sounds legitimate.

The gentleman behind the counter (David) told me that he has my car and I cannot get it back now until I pay cash, that he has the power to not accept my credit card and that the only way I can get my car back is to pay cash (pretty shady if you cannot backup your claims to a credit dispute and demand cash in my opinion). Well I haven't carried around cash with me for the last 10 years, so on top of the entire bad experience he wanted me to go walking around (he has my car) to go find an ATM down the street (Very poor customer service if you ask me). After 15 minutes of back and forth he finally accepted to take my credit card and I left not a very happy customer.

I drove right down the street to Star Station Smog to find out that my claims were true and that I passed the smog test in 15 minutes!! and it was cheaper. Star Station Smog also told me that if I would have failed they would perform re-tests for FREE! (Aero Auto didn't even want to give me a discount for smog re-test that failed because the battery was disconnected).

In the end it wasn't so much of the pass/fail that was so disappointing but just the lack of customer service (but the $80 failed test that didn't have to fail does sting). There are ways you can offer assistance to help build a good customer/shop relationship and I didn't see any from my experience today.

If you need a smog, take my advice and go down the street to Star Station Smog you won't be disappointed (and no I do not work for them, but just had an amazing experience with how courteous and professional they are) .</review>< Resp>

< user>
114081840794408167454</user>
<user_name>AM P< /user_name><date>1485627901090<//date>< rating>
3</rating>
< review>
I rented this space in a rush and didn't look at it ahead. The building is clean and secure, with large elevators. The office staff are nice.

But the ceilings are only 8' high and the lighting is awful. The area between lockers on each side is narrow, making it a puzzle to get larger items situated. My movers were frustrated and they're experienced.

The motion sensor lights turn off after just a few minutes and you have to go down the hall, wave your arms to turn them on. Previously, I've had drive up storage and this was never an issue. Bring a flashlight!

The building is COLD. Dress for winter. It never gets sun and the cement holds intense, bone numbing cold. It's good for my stuff, so I bring a jacket and gloves even to just run in for a couple of things. They will all be ice cold.

I'm not a fan of the limited hours. Traffic at rush hour makes it hard to get to get there during the week. The early daily close is a pain. The 9pm close at my former storage area was really handy.< /review>

< review>
I was so happy to find Security Public Storage. They are amazing in every single way:

1.Great customer service! I usually interact with Steve who is always very helpful. He always does what he can to offer you the best deals.

2. This place has the best deals! I looked around and no other self-storage place could compare.

3. They let you use a moving truck to move your stuff into storage. I saved at least $100 alone from this service.

4. Storage units are inside the building and protected from the elements, rain, etc. and are typically 20degrees lower than the weather outside.
It is even printed from rodents and pests.

5. They have security cameras, and individual alarms for each unit and have never had a breakin and have been open for 31 years.

6. It is located off El Camino, which is super convenient. They have a gate and a personal code to get in. It is a super safe area, which is really important to me.

7. There is always someone in the office to help you with whatever you need.

8. They have a huge 10x15  freight elevator.

9. They have 7 carts so no need to really carry things in and out.

I love this place and have used their service for 5 months. I'm super glad I did my research and was able to find the best storage company in the area!< /review>

<review>I was extremely impressed by this place. It's kind of like Chipotle but with more authentic Mexican flavor and ingredients. You go through the line to custom build tacos, burritos or bowls. It has all kinds of interesting toppings to choose from, like mango pico de gallo, Mexican cheese, and pickled onions. The carne asada and shrimp were delicious and they served chips and salsa along with the meal. They also had some refreshing infused waters and a complete bar.

The place is clean, modern looking and has some beautiful artwork painted on the walls that reminds me of dia los muertos murals. The kitchen/counter is bright and evenly lit, while the dining area is surrounded by the decor and has slightly moodier lighting. The staff was responsive and friendly. This was a very pleasant place to get a quick meal.</review>< Pictures>

< review>
Stumbled onto this place accidentally, while looking for another restaurant. It seemed inviting, with multiple patrons dining at tables on the little side patio outdoors. We ordered their individual tacos, which were good-sized, & you get to choose all the ingredients. We had ours loaded with carne asada, rice, black beans, salsa, sour cream, cheese, & more. They were mouth watering! Served with chips & salsa on the side, at no extra charge. They have a variety of meats, including pork & chicken. Loved this place, & we will definitely go back again!</review>

<Text>The guys came to Livermore for the first time to visit me (I'm always driving down to San Jose to visit them), so I needed to take them somewhere really good. Cinco TacoBar delivered, and even my picky-eater-type friends polished off their burritos. I'm a big fan of build-your-own-burrito places, and this place delivers in spades, with a large number of fillings. In particular, this is the first time I've encountered a place serving fresh queso! Obviously, there were other things on the menu, but I went with the burrito. The horchata hit the spot right after lunch! Pro tip: Get it without ice, you'll get way more of your drink. Great place for lunch, maybe a bit on the pricey side.<//Text>< Pictures>

<Rating>5</Rating>< Review>
A great spot for a Friday work lunch. Get here early or late, cause it's always busy. Nice mix of seating, decor and ambiance are nice. The food is the real star here. Made to order tacos, quesadillas, burritos etc with a vast array of customizable toppings. I've liked all the fillings I've tried, but the surprise standout is the grilled veggie mix. Corn, zucchini, peppers, tomatoes and onions with beautiful carmelization, great in a taco or quesadilla. It's a good, filling lunch at a good price.</Review>

< text>
One of the few legit, Japanese run and owned sushi restaurants around. Appreciate the quality of the seafood and daily specials. I used to complain about the attitude and service, but that is now a thing of the past. Service was friendly and efficient during times of Covid. Nothing was missing from our order and everything tasted fantastic. Should not have waited so long to come back. Will be part of my regular rotation now that we have rediscovered this place.< /text>

<user_id>101531888333513545623</user_id>< Rating>

</record></dataset><record>
< pics>
None<//pics>
<Resp>None<//Resp>< rate>
4</rate>
<GmapID>0x80c328522c43f14d:0xe7f567eeabff7863<//GmapID>< name>
Jennifer Hunker<//name>
< Time>
1473457907345<//Time>
< Text>
WHAT IT IS
Sushi restaurant and bar. They also have your typical bento combinations and "kitchen" meals. A tip: Parking is behind the restaurant.

WHAT YOU SHOULD ORDER
Sushi!

AMBIANCE
4 stars
It's a fairly basic Japanese restaurant. When you enter from the street you, will be in a small foyer with tables all around you. To your right you will see the sushi bar. They have a few TVs on the walls as well. The music both times I've gone in is American, which is sort of unique for these sorts of places.

FOOD AND DRINKS
4 Stars
Both times I've been here I ordered the Nigiri plate which comes with a california roll and 8 pieces of assorted nigiri. The sushi here is fairly good. It's nothing that will blow you away, but it's fresh and doesn't commit any "cardinal sushi sins". I prefer a bit more vinegar in my rice.

The nigiri have a good fish to rice ratio. The fish cuts are thick, so you get a good amount of fish for your buck.The rice is sticky and holds up well. None of my nigiri fell apart upon being picked up. This is hugely important in a western sushi restaurant as I'm embarrassed to eat the nigiri properly (with my fingers) and opt to use the chopsticks instead. Nothing is worse than watching as the rice falls apart when you try to pick up your nigiri!

There was a good assortment of nigiri as well--8 different flavors! They were all delicious.

The California Roll was the lowpoint--the filling lacked flavor and there was a bit too much celery. It wasn't awful, but it was nothing to write home about.

The meal also comes with miso soup and a small salad. The salad is good. I don't know what's in their dressing, but I like it. Aside from that it's just your basic salad--iceburg lettuce and some red cabbage. The miso soup was another nice surprise--it was so flavorful! The tofu in it was wonderful too--soft and fresh. I've had SO many bad tofu cubes in miso soup over the years, so it's awesome to find a place that puts fresh tofu in their soup!

NICE SURPRISES
The assortment of Nigiri with the special is a nice touch, especially because many of the places around here limit you to 4 varieties of fish with these types of combos (opting to give you two of each instead). The miso soup was also a delight.

OVERALL
This is a great place for lunch. The service is quick--both lunches took me just under 40 minutes (and both times the restaurant was crowded.) You can call ahead and pick up your order too.< /Text>
<UserId.>106304859915860891916</UserId.></record></dataset><record>
